# Infrastructure as Code: Automating Windows Domain Controller Deployments

## Project Objective
Eliminate manual errors and scale corporate environment blueprints by deploying a
cloud-based Active Directory Domain Controller entirely through automated 
boot scripting.

## System Design
Instead of executing standard GUI configurations via Server Manager, this architecture 
leverages the AWS EC2 configuration lifecycle mechanism (`User Data`) to inject 
low-level administrative PowerShell sequences during early initialization cycles.

## Code Architecture
The deployment infrastructure utilizes the standard `Install-ADDSForest` command string 
wrapped inside system processing tags:


```script```
<powershell>
# 1. Install Active Directory Domain Services Role
Install-WindowsFeature -Name AD-Domain-Services -IncludeManagementTools

# 2. Define the Domain Configuration Parameters
$DomainName = "homelab.local"
$NetbiosName = "HOMELAB"

# 3. Create a Secure Password for the DSRM Restore Account
# Change "your_own_password" to your own secure password string
$DSRMFilePassword = ConvertTo-SecureString "your_own_password" -AsPlainText -Force

# 4. Execute the Forest Promotion (Automates the Server Manager Wizard)
Install-ADDSForest `
    -DomainName $DomainName `
    -CreateDnsDelegation:$false `
    -DatabasePath "C:\Windows\NTDS" `
    -LogPath "C:\Windows\NTDS" `
    -SysVolPath "C:\Windows\SYSVOL" `
    -NoRebootOnCompletion:$false `
    -Force:$true `
    -SafeModeAdministratorPassword $DSRMFilePassword

</powershell>
```
